hievements that have garnered numerous awards including canada’s top  under  alberta’s most influential top  people ernst and young’s entrepreneur of the year and the certificate of merit for business excellence by industry science and technology canada greg rude director of corporate sales greg rude director of corporate sales greg rude has over  years of experience selling industrial safety products and services into the north american marketplace greg was the north american business development manager at bw technologies before becoming the western zone manager following the acquisition of bw technologies by honeywell greg took on the role of national sales manager at honeywell analytics clark swanson director business development americas clark swanson director business development americas clark swanson previously held an executive position for sourcecode technology holdings inc a global software firm headquartered in redmond washington mr swanson has also served as executive vice president of universal studios based white eagle productions and director of immedient corporation a software services company headquartered in mountain view california mr swanson holds a degree in economics from pepperdine university and also graduated honors from the graziadio school of business  management with an mba emphasis in finance bernadette geronazzo director of public  investor relations bernadette geronazzo director of public  investor relations bernadette geronazzo is an accredited business communicator with more than  years of experience in corporate communication plans advertising and raising awareness for corporations with targeted audiences she has worked with clients that range from independent business owners to multinational corporations in the areas of public and investor relations marketing strategic planning as well as nonprofit and community relations she has codirected and written for television has been a columnist for the calgary herald as well as the calgary real estate board and has worked in the role of executive director for a business revitalization zone in calgary brendon cook chief technology officer  cofounder brendon cook chief technology officer  cofounder brendon cook was awarded a bsc in geomatics engineering from the university of calgary prior to founding blackline gps inc in  mr cook worked for calgarybased csi wireless inc now hemisphere gps inc as its product and marketing manager and developed business relationships with various international organizations at csi wireless inc mr cook managed the company’s precision product portfolio and was responsible for the market analysis generating market analysis generating market direction defining new products and assisted with managing the company’s product development program board members blackline’s devoted board members support and guide our business cody slater ceo  chairman blackline safety corp calgary ab ca michael hayduk consulting lawyer  director calgary ab ca dr john finbow director retired canmore ab ca robert j herdman director retired calgary ab ca brad gilewich director senior vp corporate affairs at the katz group edmonton ab ca want to learn more we provide tools that enable employers to improve the outcome for workers who have suffered a safety incident health issue or physical assault we don’t prevent incidents but we are there to make the most of difficult and dangerous situations how can we help your organization blackline safety gx achieves final certifications now shipping tsx venture exchangebln english français register sign in blackline safety gx achieves final certifications now shipping gx plus singlegas and quadgas cartridges with ‘lel’ sensor approved for use in hazardous locations july    et  source blackline safety corp photorelease gx wireless gas detection and lone worker monitoring system for remote employees gx plus singlegas and quadgas cartridges with ‘lel’ sensor approved for use in hazardous locations blackline safety corp calgary alberta july   globe newswire  blackline safety tsx venturebln blackline has achieved all required certifications for its new gx wireless gas detection and lone worker monitoring system for remote employees blackline’s complete g product line is fullycertified and shipping globally a photo accompanying this announcement is available at httpwwwglobenewswirecomnewsroomattachmentngfcaeefacecedaf all electronic equipment used in hazardous locations must be certified intrinsically safe to prevent a potential for atmospheric explosion due to the presence of combustible gases or vapors additionally the north american marketplace requires a performance certification for gas detection equipment fitted with a combustible gas sensor the full g family now carries these certifications and can be used by workers in all hazardous environments “our new gx employeeworn satelliteconnected safety device is now the latest g safety product to meet these high standards” said cody slater ceo and chairman at blackline safety “our full g product family is now bringing stateoftheart emergency response management to industries and work scenarios where every second counts wireless safety monitoring empowers every business to put their teams first and act in realtime to make the difference between rescue and recovery” gx is a highly customizable gas detection instrument that empowers the fastest possible emergency response — directly to an employee’s location however remote they are featuring internal location technology and automatic incident detection capabilities gx alerts live monitoring personnel when an employee requires help gx is the only quad gas instrument with satellite communications and twoway messaging to the employee connecting a live monitoring team with a worker in need of assistance twoway messaging allows monitoring personnel to assess the situation and deploy an emergency response as required in remote locations coworkers are often the first responders and can be dispatched to the employee’s exact location and are notified to prepare for any atmospheric hazards such as a gas leak gx is the only wireless gas detector to feature a series of fieldreplaceable cartridges tailoring operation for environmental gas detection lone worker monitoring and evacuation management scenarios singlegas and quadgas cartridges support a lower explosive limit lel sensor to detect combustible gases industries where personnel enter confined spaces often leverage a quadgas instrument with combustible gas hydrogen sulfide hs carbon monoxide co and oxygen o sensors as a twopart solution gx works in conjunction with blackline’s g bridge portable satellite base station to deliver true lastmile safety monitoring of remote personnel the g bridge base station manages a satellite uplink to the blackline safety network facilitating safety monitoring of field personnel through a cloudhosted portal an industrialquality radio link connects up to five gx devices to one g bridge and delivers a realworld open range of two kilometers this  mhz radio link enables monitored employees to confidently move from driving a vehicle to working throughout complex facilities without interruption gx has achieved certification for its lel sensor construction performance and test according to csa c no m r combustible gas detection instruments and ansiisas  performance requirements for combustible gas detectors gx is also certified intrinsically safe in north america with a class i division  groups a b c and d rating and according to iexex ex ia iic t ga to learn more about blacklines employee safety monitoring solutions visit wwwblacklinesafetycom and follow blackline on twitter blacklinesafety about blackline safety blackline safety is a global connected safety technology leader providing comprehensive livemonitoring and wireless gas detection we help teams working in hazardous environments respond to emergencies in realtime and manage efficient evacuations accounting for everyone’s safety along the way with millions invested in technology research and development blackline safety is recognized for quality and innovation our talented team of designers and engineers create and manufacture everything inhouse — from wearable technology and personal gas detectors to cloudhosted infrastructure and webbased interfaces for global industry we deliver the world’s first turnkey workanywhere connected safety monitoring solution with gas detection g wireless satellite communications twoway speakerphone employee messaging and live monitoring to meet the demanding safety challenges of organizations in over  countries for more information visit wwwblacklinesafetycom neither tsx venture exchange nor its regulation services provider as that term is defined in the policies of the tsx venture exchange accepts responsibility for the adequacy or accuracy of this release cody slater ceo cslaterblacklinesafetycom   blackline safety corp unit    street se calgary ab canada tg j telephone     fax     wwwblacklinesafetycom related articles more articles issued by blackline safety corp more articles related to product  services announcement profile blackline safety corp   subscribe via rss  subscribe via atom  javascript calgary alberta canada   httpwwwblacklinegpscom contact data cody slater ceo cslaterblacklinesafetycom   blackline safety corp unit    street se calgary ab canada tg j telephone     fax     wwwblacklinesafetycom contact with a reader account its easy to send email directly to the contact for this release sign up today for your free reader account already have an account log in here media files gx wireless gas detection and lone worker monitoring system for remote employees png   x  image url  copy the link below gx plus singlegas and quadgas cartridges with ‘lel’ sensor approved for use in hazardous locations blackline safety corp formats available original large medium small blackline safety corp logo logo url  copy the link below formats avai